##If you are a fevered pregnant woman in Xiaogan, Hubei Province

Micro signal

Function description, we are with you in this battle

At a time when the new type of coronary pneumonia is rampant, pregnant women with fever are in an awkward position in Xiaogan: The obstetrics and Gynecology Department does not accept pregnant women with fever, the fever clinic does not accept pregnant women, the hospitals push each other away, they can not get treatment.

By Wu Meifen

On January 22, Zou Jie (not his real name) , who works in Wuhan, and his wife, who is four months pregnant, returned to their hometown of Xiaogan for the Spring Festival. On February 14, his wife had a sudden fever, and for the next five days they spent two or three rounds in the obstetrics and gynaecology departments and fever clinics of various hospitals in Xiaogan.

When I contacted Zou on Feb. 17, they were being examined at Xiaogan Central Hospital and were advised to have a CT scan to determine if they had a COVID-19 infection, but a CT scan could cause fetal malformation, mr. and Mrs. Zou are in a dilemma.

I asked Zou why he chose not to have a nucleic acid test. He said there was a shortage of nucleic acid reagents, and local hospitals had to have CT results before they could do nucleic acid tests. Very helpless, February 19, Mr. and Mrs. Zou Jie had to choose home quarantine observation. The same day, he gave me an interview.

Here's Zou's take:

On Valentine's night,

My pregnant wife was taken to a quarantine facility

On February 14th, the night of Valentine's Day, my wife had a fever of 102. Because she was now 18 weeks pregnant, and I was a little worried about her fever, so I rushed her to the Tam Giang Space Hospital in Xiaogan.

We went to the fever clinic, after arriving, the staff first asked some basic information about us. As soon as they heard that we were pregnant women with fever, they said directly: "We do not accept pregnant women here. ". Then we went to the First Hospital of Xiaogan City, or not. I asked them, where do you accept it? They said Xiaogan City Center hospital, which is the new crown pneumonia designated hospital.

Then we drove to the Central Hospital, but the Central Hospital said they don't take pregnant women, let's go to the Maternity Hospital. I'm getting a little tired of hospitals pushing me around. No way, or drive to the maternity hospital to try, to there is already more than eight o'clock at night, my wife is still high fever, food did not eat.

The wife sat in Xiaogan City Center Hospital and communicated with the results

The doctor of the woman and Child Hospital hears my wife is having a fever, say directly: "Here does not receive to have a fever crowd" . I had nowhere else to go, so I asked her to take a look at it. The doctor took my wife's temperature. After taking the temperature, they didn't do any other tests, said they couldn't do it, not even a blood test, because they couldn't treat people with fever. I said no tests. Can I have some medicine? The doctor said he'd put us in touch, so he called.

It was raining that night, the temperature was low, and my wife had a high fever. I was anxious. After the doctor called, he told us he wanted us to go to quarantine, and that there might be paramedics at the quarantine site. I feel uneasy after hearing, then continue to implore, can do a test first, let me know what the situation, in the mind have a calm.

The doctor insisted he couldn't do it. He had to go to the quarantine.

We can't. State policy says we can't as citizens. Well, in that case, I thought we'd go home for dinner. But the doctor said, "No, there's food in the quarantine. We have to go now. ".

At the quarantine point, I can't go in. My wife went in alone. When she checked in, she found it was a temporary quarantine for the commandeered dormitories of local businesses, with no medical staff, no food, no supervision, just basic supplies in each room.

When my wife told me about it, I was devastated. The doctor of woman and Child Hospital knows my wife has a fever, also did not think what method can let her reduce a fever. As a doctor, he at least knew how much a fever affected the pregnant woman and the fetus. Not only is there no medicine, there's not even the slightest physical cooling, and they just drop us off at the isolation point, which I don't think any normal person could handle.

Fortunately, my wife spent the night at the quarantine point, and although it was cold, her temperature returned to normal the next morning.

"Hot Potato. "

In the morning, maternal and Child Hospital doctors contacted me, let me to maternal and child hospital to open a certificate, take the certificate to quarantine point pick up, and then come to maternal and child hospital. But when I arrived at the hospital, the other director in charge said the hospital could not issue a certificate, let me go to quarantine point to ask clear procedures, and then the hospital and Quarantine Point Communication. I was a little confused. Wasn't this supposed to be a communication between the hospital and the quarantine? Why do I have to go?

Xiaogan women and children's hospital, taken by Zou Jie on Feb. 15

By then the city road in Xiaogan had been closed, and there were traffic police on the road, so I couldn't drive out. The doctor advised me to go to the community to open a certificate, with the certificate can pass the traffic police checkpoint, then I was very worried, according to their way to the community opened a certificate, his car to the quarantine point. The staff at the quarantine point told me that I needed permission from the head of the local hospital to get my wife out. So I called the doctor at the Maternity Hospital.

The doctor worked on the matter for a whole morning, constantly help us to communicate, it can be seen that she would like to help us, but also just stay in communication, there is no effective solution. An hour later, a 120 ambulance arrived. I thought the ambulance was to take us to the maternity and children's hospital, finally found him to take us to the First Hospital of Xiaogan city.

Xiaogan first hospital doctors after receiving muddled, they said how come this pregnant woman again, was not rejected at that time, how come again. Hospitals are chaotic when it comes to taking in patients, bouncing the balls off each other.

My wife is devastated by something like this.

I had to. I begged them to at least check it out. Medical did a blood test on us. At noon on February 15, we had our first blood test. The results showed that the white blood cells were very high and the situation was very bad. The doctor's preliminary judgment was that it might be a bacterial infection. It is recommended that we do a CT SCAN for further verification.

We all know that pregnant women are at high risk of having a CT scan, which can lead to fetal malformation. My wife and I don't want a C.T. We would rather be infected with a new coronary pneumonia than risk the birth of a future child that may be deformed. But the doctor said no CT diagnosis, had to recommend that we transfer, to the space hospital or Maternity Hospital to see if there is any way.

Her advice doesn't make sense, because we've already run through the hospitals. I'm hoping she can help us get in touch with the hospitals, and we'll head over there. Otherwise, they won't take it, and the ball's going around.

The doctor said that if you talk to the director, there's no follow-up.

After a long day, we didn't eat. Finally we said to the doctor, can give us some fever medicine, we go home for dinner first observation.

When we got home, we did physical cooling with ice cubes and cold towels. For the next few days, my wife didn't have a fever during the day, but in the afternoon her temperature would rise, and in the evening it would be above 37.5 degrees.

On February 18th, my wife had been running a fever for five days. I decided I couldn't wait any longer, so I called 96120 and they put me in touch with the local health clinic. But the hospital said there is no condition for pregnant women to do relevant tests, let us go to the Central Hospital or maternity and Child Hospital.

I felt the whole process was extremely cumbersome, so I asked 120 reasons. 120 says they run the district, and the hospital in the neighborhood is the health center, so 120 can only send us to the health center, and the Health Center doesn't have access to pregnant women with fever, so 120 can't send us.

At the time, I was furious. Weren't there pregnant women among the tens of thousands already infected? Does a pregnant woman deserve to die from a fever?

In this case, no way, we can only rely on their ability to contact the hospital network. That day we ran to the space hospital, or the same excuse, said no conditions, special period must follow the procedure.

Obstetrics and gynecology is not because of fever, fever clinic is not because pregnant women.

Finally, 120 helped us contact the space hospital, Space Hospital helped us contact the central hospital.

When we arrived at the Central Hospital, the doctor took five minutes to register us and get our personal medical history. About an hour later, their advice to us was to get a CT scan.

It's a real headache. There's no way we're getting a CT scan. Now I just want my fever to go down and take some anti-inflammatories. We also know that taking anti-inflammatory drugs, intravenous drip on the fetal impact, but the impact of CT radiation is too great.

Usually no new coronavirus, not all pregnant women have a fever to do CT.. The doctors didn't give us any tests, so they just kept going on about it. The doctor listened to my theory, have nothing to say, say to give us a preliminary blood test.

I asked my doctor if I could do a nucleic acid test, and the hospital said no, you have to do a CT to do a nucleic acid test. I think it would be safer if we could get a nucleic acid test.

On Feb. 18, doctors at the Central People's Hospital helped with the exam

Fortunately, the blood test showed that my wife's vitals were normal, except for the low lymphocyte. Finally the doctor gave us two boxes of CEPHALOSPORINS and told us to go home and Quarantine.

Observation Room of Xiaogan Central Hospital

In the meantime, each department of the government only wants to solve their own things, and keep me informed, but only limited to process and communication, no real action to solve the problem. But the patient's condition continues to deteriorate, the treatment is urgent.

I hope that in such a special period, the relevant departments of Xiaogan can take special measures and means for special groups, to protect the issue of medical treatment for special groups, not one-size-fits-all, regardless of the actual situation.

Families are being sent to quarantines

Although the possibility of COVID-19 infection has been largely ruled out, the community has asked us to impose quarantine. Considering my wife was pregnant, they let me stay home with her, so I put my parents and my sister in isolation.

To be honest, I'm a little freaked out about putting normal people in my house who don't have symptoms in isolation. Because the isolation of the hotel environment is very bad, particularly unsanitary, toilet stains, bed hair and cigarette butts, it is clear that there is no cleaning and disinfection.

What pisses me off even more is that this segregated hotel is full of people. With a fever and a highly suspicious patient, and with such poor hygiene, it's a higher risk than if we went outside. Let my old man live there for 14 days, if something goes wrong, who's responsible?

Now that the government's forcing us to go to the quarantine, we'll cooperate. But at the very least, the government needs to be able to take responsibility for segregation and get the job done. It was an unconvincing environment.

From my personal experience as an ordinary person, the ability and logic of the local government in the prevention and control of this epidemic is not common sense, there is a sense of their own formalism in the inside, isolation does not play the role of isolation.

February 22,5:00 p.m. , I took my wife's temperature, she found that a fever. I contacted the community leaders, the community arranged to send us to the hospital, I think this time to the hospital is not appropriate, because before the hospital, they said there is no medical conditions for testing or treatment. But the community insisted that we go, and on the way to the hospital, my wife had a high fever, shaking, fainting symptoms.

5:45, we arrived at the health center, when the doctor began to take the temperature, I said people are now very sick, to faint. The doctor said he couldn't get me 96120. I mean, isn't that pointless? Drag people in here and wait. The doctor responded that they were following procedure.

They did everything by the book, but the patient couldn't wait, and while they waited, my wife started vomiting. Three PUKES, high temperature to 39.3 degrees, a blood test in the middle, the results are not very good, immune cells basically zero, is critically ill people.

The doctor told me that it's not a question of new pneumonia, or whether to protect children or adults, and that both children and adults are at risk.

The health department put us in touch with the car and waited until eight o'clock. They said they would take us to the district maternity and children's hospital. I was more worried that the women and children's Hospital in the district wouldn't take us because that was the case before. I then contacted the community leaders, the community said to the maternity and children's hospital said, if the maternity and children's hospital does not accept, they will try to find a way.

I think it's ridiculous. It's just a formality. If you go there and wait two hours for nothing, you're playing with your life.

Fortunately, the ambulance came from the Central Hospital. They said that if the women and children's Hospital didn't accept it, they could go to the central hospital.

Finally we went to the Central Hospital for tests, the results were very bad, people are very dangerous, no immunity. We were waiting outside for the results, and the hospital said we had to do a CT today. I hope they get rid of my wife's high fever as soon as possible. But has been on and off to carry out various tests, until until more than eleven in hospital.

After my wife moved in, I wanted to go home and get something to eat, but I didn't have a car, so I had to walk 14 kilometers. Drove back to the hospital at 2:30 in the morning for a CT scan. The CT scan ruled out that my wife has neocoronary pneumonia.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At midnight on Feb. 23, Zou's walk home was empty

From the 14th to now, I will receive every day city epidemic prevention, district epidemic prevention, community epidemic prevention, 120 and other departments of inquiry calls, but I think little effect. You can't cure a disease with a phone call, you can't cure a fever with a phone call, you can't cure a patient.

In the end, we did all the tests we needed to do, we did the CT, but the fever wasn't treated. I don't know what Darling's problems are going to be, what her health is going to be like.
